spans.text: stand forth his brawny arm to boast
Whoever the quoit can wield , And furthest send its weight athwart the field
at the word , from out the gazing host Young Pterelas with strength unequal drew
The band around admire the mighty mass
your arms shall raze the Tyrian towers
Who trust your arms shall raze the Tyrian towers
The ponderous brass in exercise he bore
flowed the widest stream he took his stand ; Sure flew the disc from his unerring hand , Nor stopped till it had cut the further strand
its weight , elusive of his hold
fitting to his grip and nervous arm , Suspends the crowd with animation warm , Nor tempts he yet the plain but , hurled upright , Emits the mass , a prelude of his might
Their cymbals toss and sounding brass explore
her dreadful hour , And smiles malignant on the labouring power
With sturdy step and slow , Hippomedon
all his nerves and every sinew strung
all his nerves and every sinew strung
joys to see Its ancient lord secure of victory
Its ancient lord secure of victory

The eyeless Cyclops heaved the craggy rock : Where ocean frets beneath the dashing oar , And parting surges round the vessel roar , 'Twas there he aimed the meditated harm , And scarce Ulysses escaped his giant arm
